183&ndash;210.</li>

<li>Roadevin, C., 2018, &ldquo;Hypocritical Blame, Fairness, and
Standing&rdquo;, <em>Metaphilosophy</em>, 49: 137&ndash;152.</li>

<li>Robichaud, P. and J. W. Wieland. (eds.), 2017, <em>Responsibility:
The Epistemic Condition</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>Rosen, G., 2004, &ldquo;Skepticism about Moral
Responsibility&rdquo;, <em>Philosophical Perspectives</em>, 18:
295&ndash;313.</li>

<li>Sabini, J. and M. Silver, 1982, <em>Moralities of Everyday
Life</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>Sars, N., 2023, &ldquo;Blame, Nudging, and the Actual Moral
Relationship&rdquo;, <em>International Journal of Philosophical
Studies</em>, 31: 18&ndash;35.</li>

<li>Scanlon, T. M., 1986, &ldquo;The Significance of Choice&rdquo;,
